- 'a decade ago' refers to the year 2010;
- 'NSF' stands for National Science Foundation;
- 'last year' refers to the year 2021.

sql:
SELECT faculty.name AS identity, departments.department_name AS division
FROM faculty
JOIN departments ON faculty.department_id = departments.department_id;

SELECT f.name
FROM faculty f
WHERE LENGTH(f.research_statement) - LENGTH(REPLACE(f.research_statement, ' ', '')) + 1 < 200;

external_knowledge:
- "academics" refers to faculty members;
- "exploring topics in the realm of computer science" means their research interests fall under the 'Computer Science' category;
- "backing from the NIH" means the funding agency providing grants is 'NIH'.

- 'Proactive researchers' are those who have a high activity ratio;
- Activity ratio is calculated as the average of three measures: interest ratio, publication ratio, and grant ratio;
- 'Hired after 2005' means the date of hiring is after January 1, 2005.
